<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 6:47PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Rogers,
east central Osage, southern Washington, southwestern Nowata and
north central Tulsa Counties through 715 PM CDT...
At 647 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
southeast of Avant, moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Bartlesville...                   Skiatook...
Barnsdall...                      Ramona...
Ochelata...                       Avant...
Talala...                         Vera...
Watova...                         Wolco...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for northeastern
Oklahoma.</instruction>
